&lt;p&gt;Black Canyon Consulting &lt;strong&gt;(BCC)&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;is searching for a&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Full-Stack Developer&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;to support the User Services and Collection Division&amp;nbsp;(USCD),&amp;nbsp;part of the U.S. National Library of Medicine, National Institutes of Health. The USCD is responsible for managing the NLM&#39;s extensive collection of biomedical literature, health information, and data resources. Its core mandate is to&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;collect, curate, and connect&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;the world to this information.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The&amp;nbsp;Full-Stack Developer&amp;nbsp;will work on DailyMed. &lt;a href=&quot;https://dailymed.nlm.nih.gov/dailymed/about-dailymed.cfm&quot;&gt;DailyMed&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;is&amp;nbsp;a free, official National Institutes of Health (NIH) National Library of Medicine (NLM) resource providing the most current drug labeling (package inserts) for prescription and over-the-counter medicines, medical devices, and gases, directly from the FDA. Managed by the NLM, it serves as a comprehensive, user-friendly database for patients, clinicians, and researchers to access standardized, up-to-date information on dosages, warnings, interactions, and more, supporting public health.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This opportunity is full-time and involves working with the USCD team in Bethesda, MD.&lt;/p&gt;
