&lt;h2 class=&quot;iCIMS_InfoMsg iCIMS_InfoField_Job&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: large;&quot;&gt;Overview&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Black Canyon Consulting &lt;strong&gt;(BCC)&lt;/strong&gt;is searching for a&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Full-Stack Developer&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;to support the User Services and Collection Division&amp;nbsp;(USCD),&amp;nbsp;part of the U.S. National Library of Medicine, National Institutes of Health. The USCD is responsible for managing the NLM&#39;s extensive collection of biomedical literature, health information, and data resources. Its core mandate is to&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;collect, curate, and connect&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;the world to this information.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The&amp;nbsp;Full-Stack Developer&amp;nbsp;will work on RxNorm. RxNorm is a standardized naming system for U.S. prescription and over-the-counter drugs, providing &quot;normalized&quot; names (ingredient + strength + form) and unique codes to resolve naming confusion between different systems, enabling clear drug identification and data sharing in EHRs and research. It links brand names to generics, helping computers and people understand the same medication unambiguously.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This opportunity is full-time and involves working with the USCD team in Bethesda, MD.&lt;/p&gt;
